## OS
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

## Editors
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp
*~

## Python
__pycache__/
*.pyc
.venv/

## Local builds — packages/ IS committed (PixInsight needs to fetch
## them via raw URL), so do NOT ignore packages/.
## But ignore any incidental tarballs left at the repo root.
/*.tar.gz
/*.zip

## Claude / IDE scratch
.claude/

## Signing keys - NEVER commit these. The .xssk file contains your
## encrypted private signing key; if it leaks together with the
## password, someone can forge signatures under your identity.
*.xssk

## .xsgn signature sidecars SHOULD be committed - they're the public
## proof that a specific .js was signed by you. This rule un-ignores
## them in case a broader pattern above matches.
!*.xsgn
